<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 7. Elytral punctures and coloration: a in rows in deep striae, Pachybrachis luctuosus b confused in basal half, in rows in apical half, Pachybrachis calcaratus c all confused, Pachybrachis hepaticus d confused and mottled, Pachybrachis spumarius e vittate with marginal vitta interrupted, Pachybrachis bivattatus f black, margined with yellow, Pachybrachis nigriconis carbonarius g entirely black, Pachybrachis luridus." , "Map 2. The known distribution of Pachybrachis bivittatus in eastern Canada. OR - Ottawa River; SLR - St. Lawrence River; SR - Saguenay River." , "Figure 8. Pygidium: a largely yellow, Pachybrachis bivittatus b with well-defined yellow spots, Pachybrachis cephalicus c with faint reddish spots, Pachybrachis spumarius d black, Pachybrachis atomarius." , "Figure 6. Pronotum: a reddish, with close-up of marginal bead, Pachybrachis bivittatus b mottled, Pachybrachis spumarius c with black M-mark, Pachybrachis m-nigrum d almost black, Pachybrachis nigricornis carbonarius." , "Figure 9. Sexes: a male abdomen, ventral view, Pachybrachis bivittatus b female abdomen, ventral view, Pachybrachis bivittatus." , "Habitus 2. Dorsal habitus of Pachybrachis bivittatus. Scale bar, 1 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/20863" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/20930" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/20866" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/20867" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/20906" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/20864" .

